  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want all commits that make it into develop to be code signed by a core contributor's PGP key so that I know the certified source of changes introduced in our code base.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature/Tooling\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Write a script that automate most parts of merging a PR from an external contributor while still signing the commit from the command line.\r\n\r\nFor context: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/2611 for merge script for core contributors, and https://wiki.status.im/Code_signing_commits_into_develop.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSomething like: `./merge-external-pr.sh REMOTE BRANCH` (some manual action) and then commit shows up in `develop` branch, GPG signed by person running script and authored by person submitting initial commit.\r\n\r\nWhile it'd be nice if PR was created automatically it isn't necessary. For example script can prompt you to do action in UI and then continue once you confirmed X is done. Perhaps it ends up being two scripts, as PR needs to be reviewed with our current Github trust model.\r\n\r\nPreferably written in a similar style as `merge-sh` (short, self-contained, documented). Optional dependency: something that simplifies pull request dealings (such as hub by Github).\r\n\r\nNice to have but very optional: flow that makes external PRs appear as merged as opposed to closed. No idea how this is possibly though without introducing other branches.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEither no code signing (or Github only) or a quite cumbersome manual process as outlined in Wiki.",
